<paragraph blockId="28.[167,778,491,1083]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,530,554]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial decumbent, rhizomatous grass, 
<quantity box="[167,281,564,588]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="535" unit="cm" value="70.0" valueMax="90.0" valueMin="50.0">50–90 cm</quantity>
height. Leaf-blades inear-lanceolate acuminate, densely covered with hairs on both sides, 
<quantity box="[673,778,598,622]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.6" metricValueMax="3.6" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="28" pageNumber="535" unit="cm" value="26.0" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="16.0">16–36 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[228,345,632,656]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="11.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="28" pageNumber="535" unit="cm" value="0.85" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.6">0.6–1.1 cm</quantity>
wide, ligulate. It is identified by its typ- ical panicle, 
<quantity box="[307,415,665,689]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" metricValueMax="4.5" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="28" pageNumber="535" unit="cm" value="29.0" valueMax="45.0" valueMin="13.0">13–45 cm</quantity>
long, with hairs on the axile and glabrous spikelets.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[167,778,491,1083]" box="[168,633,738,762]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,349,738,762]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">Common name.</emphasis>
Navalinha, Capim-mirião
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="535" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="28.[167,778,491,1083]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,279,778,802]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">Remarks.</emphasis>
A uncommon species, occurring sparsely on the native grassland.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="28.[167,778,491,1083]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,364,850,875]" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
Midwest, North (except TO state), Northeast (except MA, PI, RN and SE states), South (
<collectingRegion country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="28" pageNumber="535">PR state</collectingRegion>
) and Southeast regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
